An Act relative to Chapter 30B procurement.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 4 of chapter 30B of the General Laws is amended by striking out
2 paragraphs (a) and (b) and inserting in place thereof the following two sections:-
3 (a) Except as permitted pursuant to this section and section 7, for the procurement of a
4 supply or service in the amount of $10,000 or greater, but not more than $100,000, a
5 procurement officer shall seek written quotations from no fewer than 3 persons customarily
6 providing the supply or service. The procurement officer shall record: (1) the names and
7 addresses of all persons from whom quotations were sought, (2) the purchase description used
8 for the procurement, (3) the names of the persons submitting quotations and (4) the date and
9 amount of each quotation. Such information shall be retained in the file required pursuant to
1 of 2

10 section 3. A governmental body may require that any procurement in an amount of not more than
11 $100,000 be subject to the provisions of section 5 or section 6.
12 (b) The procurement officer shall award the contract to the responsible person offering
13 the needed quality of supply or service at the lowest quotation unless the procurement officer
14 elected to procure the supply or service subject to section 6. If the supply or service was procured
15 subject to section 6, the procurement officer shall award the contract pursuant to section 6
16 subsection (g).
